    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="797"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Harriman, W. Averell/74</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)<note n="64" xml:id="d797fn1">Addressed to the
                        Director of the Office of European Affairs (Dunn) and the Deputy Director
                        (Matthews).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-23">May 23,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In talking to me yesterday afternoon before preparing to leave to return to his
                    post, Ambassador Harriman said the President requested him to do the following: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Tell Stalin the President is still hopeful that he can find a
                            satisfactory solution to the Polish problem, that it will be kept out of
                                <pb facs="0884" n="874" xml:id="pg_874"/> “politics” and to express
                            the hope that the Soviets would give the Poles “a break”.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Discuss with Molotov the Finnish situation<note n="66"
                                xml:id="d797fn2">For correspondence regarding the failure of Finland
                                to withdraw from the war with the Soviet Union, see <ref
                                    target="frus1944v03#pg_556">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>,
                                    pp. 556</ref> ff.</note> in an endeavor to ascertain if there is
                            any other possible action which could be taken which has not already
                            been attempted.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
